name: pyxsim
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pyxsim" %}
{% set version = "4.1.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/pyxsim-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 603e8408864ddc7ea57297a7d3b1a6625c9fa698bb252bd6a4767c4d88200c5d

build:
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  number: 2

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - numpy                                  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
  host:
    - python
    - numpy
    - pip
    - cython >=0.29.21
    - setuptools >=45
    - setuptools_scm >=6.2
    - toml
    - wheel >=0.36.2
  run:
    - python
    - astropy >=4.0
    - yt >=4.1.3
    - h5py >=3.0
    - scipy
    - tqdm
    - soxs >=4.3.0
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}

test:
  imports:
    - pyxsim
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/jzuhone/pyxsim
  summary: Synthetic X-ray Emission from Astrophysical Simulations
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_file: COPYING.txt

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - jzuhone
